            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Supplies to an SEZ unit for authorised operations are zero rated under Section 16 of the IGST Act. The supplier can bill without GST under a letter of undertaking, or pay IGST and claim a refund. An endorsement from the specified officer of the zone proves the supply was for authorised operations. Domestic tariff area sales are taxed normally."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between an SEZ unit and an STPI unit for a Pune IT company?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An SEZ unit sits inside a notified zone such as the Hinjewadi park, is governed by the SEZ Act 2005, and reports to the development commissioner through monthly and annual performance returns. An STPI unit can operate from ordinary premises, registers with Software Technology Parks of India, and files SOFTEX and monthly performance reports instead. Customs benefits differ."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does an SEZ unit in Hinjewadi still get an income tax holiday under Section 10AA?",
